211008892.text: "These observations show that GEN-27 inhibits p65 nuclear translocation, which leads to the increased expression of CDX2, APC, AXIN2 and p-beta-catenin (S37), decreased nuclear translocation of beta-catenin, resulting in the down-regulation of beta-catenin target genes."
